Taraba Governor Darius Dickson Ishaku on Friday mourned the demise of former governorship candidate and frontline member of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), Aisha Jumai Alhassan. He said her death has robbed Taraba State and Nigeria of the benefits of her wealth of experience in politics. The Governor, in a statement by his Special Adviser on Media and Publicity, Bala Dan Abu, said he received with deep shock news of the death Alhassan, a former Senator. Ishaku described the deceased as a woman of great courage, adding that her death to him is a personal loss. He said he and the late Sen. Alhassan enjoyed a robust political relationship and kept in touch even while they contested Taraba governorship on different political platforms in 2015 and 2019. Describing the late Mrs. Alhassan as an asset, the Governor said her death has “robbed Taraba State and Nigeria of the benefits of her wealth of experience in politics.” The Governor said, as Minister of Women Affairs, Senator Alhassan contributed immensely towards social and political emancipation of women such her death has left a vacuum that will be difficult to fill. While praying God to grant her eternal rest, Ishaku told her family to take solace in the fact that the deceased had lived a life of service to humanity.